{"title_page": "Riviera MRT/LRT station", "text_new": "{{Infobox station\n| background      = \n| name       = {{SMRT Infobox Colour\n  | enname =  Riviera\n  | zhname = \u91cc\u7ef4\u62c9\n  | taname = \u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbe\n  | msname = Riviera\n  | lrtline = Punggol\n  | line2 = Cross Island\n  | code = {{SLRT-SMRT code 2I/C|PE|4|CP|3}}\n  | terminicode = \n}}\n | type=[[Mass Rapid Transit (Singapore)|Mass Rapid Transit]] (MRT) / [[Light Rail Transit (Singapore)|Light Rail Transit]] (LRT) station\n | image=PE4 Riviera Exit A.jpg\n | image_size=\n | image_caption=Exit A of the station\n | address=40 Punggol East<br />Singapore 828852\n | coordinates={{Coord|1|23|39.98|N|103|55|0.38|E|type:railwaystation_region:SG}}\n | other=Bus, Taxi\n | structure=Elevated\n | platform=2 ([[1 island platform]])\n | depth=\n | levels=1\n | tracks=2\n | parking=\n | bicycle=\n | passengers=\n | pass_year=\n | pass_percent=\n | pass_system=\n | opened= {{start date and age|df=yes|2005|01|29}} (Punggol LRT line)<br />{{start date and age|df=yes|2031}} (Punggol extension)\n | closed= \n | rebuilt=\n | electrified=Yes\n | ADA=Yes\n | code={{SLRT-SMRT code 2I/C|PE|4|CP|3}}\n | operator= [[SBS Transit|SBS Transit Ltd]] ([[ComfortDelGro|ComfortDelGro Corporation]]) (Punggol LRT line)\n | owned=\n | zone=\n | former=\n | services={{S-rail|title=SLRT}}{{S-line|system=SLRT|line=Punggol|branch=East|previous=Coral Edge|next=Kadaloor|circular=1|type=|type2=|notemid=}}\n{{S-rail-next|title=SMRT}}{{S-line|system=SMRT|line=Cross Island|branch=Punggol extension|previous=Elias|next=Punggol|notemid=Future service}}\n | mpassengers=\n | map_locator=\n}}\n\n'''Riviera MRT/LRT station (PE4/CP3)''' is an LRT station on the [[Punggol LRT line]] East Loop in [[Singapore]], located at Punggol East between the junctions of Punggol Central and Punggol Field near Punggol East Container Park. It was opened on 29 January 2005 together with the [[Sengkang LRT line|Sengkang LRT]] West Loop.\n\nBy 2031, this station will be part of a future extension between [[Pasir Ris MRT station]] and [[Punggol MRT station]] on the [[Cross Island MRT line|Cross Island line]]. However, the LRT and MRT stations will not be directly linked, similar to [[Bukit Panjang MRT/LRT station|Bukit Panjang]], [[Newton MRT station|Newton]] and [[Tampines MRT station|Tampines]] stations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/punggol-extension-cross-island-line-mrt-stations-construction-12521038|title=Punggol extension on Cross Island Line to begin construction in 2022|website=CNA|language=en|access-date=2020-03-10| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310042859/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/punggol-extension-cross-island-line-mrt-stations-construction-12521038| archive-date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n==History==\n===Punggol LRT line===\n[[File:PE4 Riviera Concourse.jpg|thumb|left|Concourse level.]]\n[[File:PE4 Riviera platforms.jpg|thumb|left|Platform level of the station.]]\nThe station was opened on 29 January 2005 together with the [[Sengkang LRT line|Sengkang LRT]] West Loop and some stations along the East loop.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sbstransit.com.sg/press/2005jan_24-1.aspx|title=Opening of Punggol LRT (East Loop) and Sengkang LRT (West Loop) |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=24 January 2005 |publisher=SBS Transit |access-date=7 September 2017 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=Punggol LRT completed|last=|first=|date=2 December 2004|work=Today|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=Punggol LRT to open on Jan 29|last=|first=|date=28 January 2005|work=Today|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n===Cross Island Line Interchange===\nOn 10 March 2020, LTA announced that Riviera station would be part of the proposed [[Cross Island MRT line|Cross Island line]] (CRL). The station will be constructed as part of Punggol extension, consisting of four stations between [[Pasir Ris MRT station|Pasir Ris]] and [[Punggol MRT/LRT station|Punggol]], and is expected to be completed in 2031.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lta.gov.sg/content/ltagov/en/newsroom/2020/march/news-releases/Cross_island_line_Punggol_extension.html|title=LTA {{!}} News Room {{!}} news-releases {{!}} Cross Island Line \u2013 Punggol Extension: Better Rail Connectivity for Punggol and Pasir Ris Residents|website=www.lta.gov.sg|access-date=2020-03-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310040156/https://www.lta.gov.sg/content/ltagov/en/newsroom/2020/march/news-releases/Cross_island_line_Punggol_extension.html|archive-date=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/punggol-residents-to-get-four-more-train-stations-by-2031|title=Punggol residents to get four more train stations by 2031|last=hermesauto|date=2020-03-10|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-10| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310040222/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/punggol-residents-to-get-four-more-train-stations-by-2031|archive-date=10 March 2020}}</ref> Construction is expected to start in 2022.\n\n<!-- Please fill in the necessary fields once the contract has been awarded--> \n<!--The Contract <Number> for the design and construction of Riviera CRL Station and associated tunnels was awarded to <company name> at a sum of S$xxx million. Construction will start in <year>, with completion in <year>.<ref> <Please reference the press/news release by LTA on their website, under press room> </ref><ref> <Please reference news outlet reports> </ref>--> \n<!-- Please fill in the necessary fields once the contract has been awarded-->\n===Incidences===\nOn 9 January 2020, at around 2.15pm, a crack was spotted on one of the elevated concrete slabs \u2014 known as [[plinths]] \u2014 on which\u00a0the LRT\u2019s light rail vehicles run. The \u201cisolated\u201d crack was located between the Riviera and Coral Edge stations. One platform has been closed early from 9pm to 4am for urgent maintenance, while operations continue as trains run on other platforms.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Eber|first=Amanda|url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/punggol-east-lrt-platform-undergoes-urgent-maintenance-after-crack-found-track?cid=h3_referral_inarticlelinks_03092019_todayonline|title=Punggol East LRT platform undergoes urgent maintenance after crack found on track|date=9 February 2020|work=Today|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Etymology==\nThe name was picked to reflect the seaside theme. It is an Italian word that means \"coastline\".\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Singapore LRT stations|punggol=yes}}\n{{Singapore MRT stations|cross-island=yes}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Riviera LRT Station}}\n[[Category:Punggol]]\n[[Category:LRT stations in Punggol]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Punggol]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 2005]]\n[[Category:Light Rail Transit (Singapore) stations]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox station\n| background      = \n| name       = {{SMRT Infobox Colour\n  | enname =  Riviera\n  | zhname = \u91cc\u7ef4\u62c9\n  | taname = \u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbe\n  | msname = Riviera\n  | lrtline = Punggol\n  | line2 = Cross Island\n  | code = {{SLRT-SMRT code 2I/C|PE|4|CP|3}}\n  | terminicode = \n}}\n | type=[[Mass Rapid Transit (Singapore)|Mass Rapid Transit]] (MRT) / [[Light Rail Transit (Singapore)|Light Rail Transit]] (LRT) station\n | image=PE4 Riviera Exit A.jpg\n | image_size=\n | image_caption=Exit A of the station\n | address=40 Punggol East<br />Singapore 828852\n | coordinates={{Coord|1|23|39.98|N|103|55|0.38|E|type:railwaystation_region:SG}}\n | other=Bus, Taxi\n | structure=Elevated\n | platform=2 ([[1 island platform]])\n | depth=\n | levels=1\n | tracks=2\n | parking=\n | bicycle=\n | passengers=\n | pass_year=\n | pass_percent=\n | pass_system=\n | opened= {{start date and age|df=yes|2005|01|29}} (Punggol LRT line)<br />{{start date and age|df=yes|2031}} (Punggol extension)\n | closed= \n | rebuilt=\n | electrified=Yes\n | ADA=Yes\n | code={{SLRT-SMRT code 2I/C|PE|4|CP|3}}\n | operator= [[SBS Transit|SBS Transit Ltd]] ([[ComfortDelGro|ComfortDelGro Corporation]]) (Punggol LRT line)\n | owned=\n | zone=\n | former=\n | services={{S-rail|title=SLRT}}{{S-line|system=SLRT|line=Punggol|branch=East|previous=Coral Edge|next=Kadaloor|circular=1|type=|type2=|notemid=}}\n{{S-rail-next|title=SMRT}}{{S-line|system=SMRT|line=Cross Island|branch=Punggol extension|previous=Elias|next=Punggol|notemid=Future service}}\n | mpassengers=\n | map_locator=\n}}\n\n'''Riviera MRT/LRT station (PE4/CP3)''' is an LRT station on the [[Punggol LRT line]] East Loop in [[Singapore]], located at Punggol East between the junctions of Punggol Central and Punggol Field near Punggol East Container Park. It was opened on 29 January 2005 together with the [[Sengkang LRT line|Sengkang LRT]] West Loop.\n\nBy 2031, this station will be part of a future extension between [[Pasir Ris MRT station]] and [[Punggol MRT station]] on the [[Cross Island MRT line|Cross Island line]]. However, the LRT and MRT stations will not be directly linked, similar to [[Bukit Panjang MRT/LRT station|Bukit Panjang]], [[Newton MRT station|Newton]] and [[Tampines MRT station|Tampines]] stations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/punggol-extension-cross-island-line-mrt-stations-construction-12521038|title=Punggol extension on Cross Island Line to begin construction in 2022|website=CNA|language=en|access-date=2020-03-10| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310042859/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/punggol-extension-cross-island-line-mrt-stations-construction-12521038| archive-date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n==History==\n===Punggol LRT line===\n[[File:PE4 Riviera Concourse.jpg|thumb|left|Concourse level.]]\n[[File:PE4 Riviera platforms.jpg|thumb|left|Platform level of the station.]]\nThe station was opened on 29 January 2005 together with the [[Sengkang LRT line|Sengkang LRT]] West Loop and some stations along the East loop.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sbstransit.com.sg/press/2005jan_24-1.aspx|title=Opening of Punggol LRT (East Loop) and Sengkang LRT (West Loop) |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=24 January 2005 |publisher=SBS Transit |access-date=7 September 2017 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=Punggol LRT completed|last=|first=|date=2 December 2004|work=Today|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=Punggol LRT to open on Jan 29|last=|first=|date=28 January 2005|work=Today|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n===Cross Island Line Interchange===\nOn 10 March 2020, LTA announced that Riviera station would be part of the proposed [[Cross Island MRT line|Cross Island line]] (CRL). The station will be constructed as part of Punggol extension, consisting of four stations between [[Pasir Ris MRT station|Pasir Ris]] and [[Punggol MRT/LRT station|Punggol]], and is expected to be completed in 2031.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lta.gov.sg/content/ltagov/en/newsroom/2020/march/news-releases/Cross_island_line_Punggol_extension.html|title=LTA {{!}} News Room {{!}} news-releases {{!}} Cross Island Line \u2013 Punggol Extension: Better Rail Connectivity for Punggol and Pasir Ris Residents|website=www.lta.gov.sg|access-date=2020-03-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310040156/https://www.lta.gov.sg/content/ltagov/en/newsroom/2020/march/news-releases/Cross_island_line_Punggol_extension.html|archive-date=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/punggol-residents-to-get-four-more-train-stations-by-2031|title=Punggol residents to get four more train stations by 2031|last=hermesauto|date=2020-03-10|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-10| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310040222/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/punggol-residents-to-get-four-more-train-stations-by-2031|archive-date=10 March 2020}}</ref> Construction is expected to start in 2022.\n\n<!-- Please fill in the necessary fields once the contract has been awarded--> \n<!--The Contract <Number> for the design and construction of Riviera CRL Station and associated tunnels was awarded to <company name> at a sum of S$xxx million. Construction will start in <year>, with completion in <year>.<ref> <Please reference the press/news release by LTA on their website, under press room> </ref><ref> <Please reference news outlet reports> </ref>--> \n<!-- Please fill in the necessary fields once the contract has been awarded-->\n===Incidences===\nOn 9 January 2020, at around 2.15pm, a crack was spotted on one of the elevated concrete slabs \u2014 known as [[plinths]] \u2014 on which\u00a0the LRT\u2019s light rail vehicles run. The \u201cisolated\u201d crack was located between the Riviera and Coral Edge stations. One platform has been closed early from 9pm to 4am for urgent maintenance, while operations continue as trains run on other platforms.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Eber|first=Amanda|url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/punggol-east-lrt-platform-undergoes-urgent-maintenance-after-crack-found-track?cid=h3_referral_inarticlelinks_03092019_todayonline|title=Punggol East LRT platform undergoes urgent maintenance after crack found on track|date=9 February 2020|work=Today|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> \nRead more at \n==Etymology==\nThe name was picked to reflect the seaside theme. It is an Italian word that means \"coastline\".\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Singapore LRT stations|punggol=yes}}\n{{Singapore MRT stations|cross-island=yes}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Riviera LRT Station}}\n[[Category:Punggol]]\n[[Category:LRT stations in Punggol]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Punggol]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 2005]]\n[[Category:Light Rail Transit (Singapore) stations]]\n", "name_user": "TheGreatSG'rean", "label": "safe", "comment": "Removed error codes.", "u