ir raid.<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|Holder|DE-401|6}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The {{sclass-|Edsall|destroyer escort|2}} was [[torpedo]]ed and damaged in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] off [[Algiers]], [[French Algeria|Algeria]] by [[Luftwaffe]] aircraft. Her crew lost 17 killed and 12 wounded. She was towed to [[Oran]] and then to [[New York City|New York]], where she was condemned. A {{convert|95|ft|m|adj=on}} section of her stern was used to repair {{USS|Menges|DE-320|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ussholder.com/DE401-Too-Short-A-Time-P2.html |title=USS Holder |publisher=www.ussholder.com |accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|M 6022 Enseigne||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[minesweeper]] was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] ({{coord|43|22|N|07|00|E}}) by {{HMS|Untiring|P59|6}} ({{navy|UK}}). 14 crew members were killed and 3 of the 12 survivors were wounded.<ref name=seekrieg194404/><ref name=Forum9867>{{cite web |url=https://www.forum-marinearchiv.de/smf/index.php?topic=9867.30 |title=M 6022 |publisher=www.forum-marinearchiv.de |accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German training ship|Mars||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[artillery]] [[training ship]] was bombed and destroyed by fire at [[Stettin]] in an American air raid.<ref name=seekrieg194404/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deutschekriegsmarine.de/hauptteil_uberwassereinheiten/hauptteil_sonderschiffe/hauptteil_schulschiffe/hauptteil_artillerieschulschif/hauptteil_artillerieschulschiffe.htm |title=Artillerieschulschiffe |publisher=www.deutschekriegsmarine.de  \u2013  Die deutsche Kriegsmarine von 1939 |accessdate=2 March 2012 |language=German}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|R-27||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=W