|08|N|128|57|E}}) by {{USS|Halibut|SS-232|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=Halibut>{{cite DANFS | title = Halibut | url = http://www.hazegray.org/danfs/submar/ss232.txt | accessdate = 1 January 2012 }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==13 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=13 April 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 565||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The Type C2 ''[[Marinef\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was sunk in the Black Sea by Soviet aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194404/><ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese destroyer|Ikazuchi|1931|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Fubuki|destroyer|2}} was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] {{convert|200|nmi|km}} south south east of Guam ({{coord|10|13|N|143|51|E}}) by {{USS|Harder|SS-257|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}). Lost with all hands.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Solvoll'' \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=World War II: The fishing vessel was shelled and sunk in the [[Norwegian Sea]] {{convert|150|nmi|km}} west of the [[Lofoten Islands]] by {{GS|U-711||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}). All eight people on board were taken on board ''U-711'' as prisoners and were held by the [[Gestapo]] until the end of the war.<ref name=Solvoll>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1756.html |title=Solvoll |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=17 April 2012}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==14 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=14 April 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|B\u00e4renfels|1921|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The cargo ship was sunk by a mine, placed by the British mini-submarine X-24, while at the coal-dock at Bergen. 11 men were killed.<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=5605537|shipname=Barenfels |accessdate=19 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?144293 |title=B\u00e4renfel