ape Spencer]] on the coast of the [[Territory of Alaska]].<ref name=alaskashipwrecksp>[https://alaskashipwreck.com/shipwrecks-a-z/alaska-shipwrecks-p/ alaskashipwreck.com Alaska Shipwrecks (P)]</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minelayer|Roland||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary [[minelayer]] struck a mine and sank in the [[Gulf of Finland]], west of the [[Kurgalsky Peninsula]] ({{coord|59|43.2|N|27|28.2|E}}).<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=5606663|shipname=Roland |accessdate=24 October 2012}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==22 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=22 April 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MS|Bahia|1927|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The cargo ship was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[North Sea]] off [[Lista]], Norway by {{HNoMS|Ula|1943|2}} ({{navy|Norway}}).<ref name=\"Berg 1997 116\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Jylland|1887|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[coastal trading vessel|coaster]] struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the [[Baltic Sea]] off [[Stralsund]], [[Mecklenburg-Vorpommern]].<ref name=seekrieg194404/><ref name=HomeJ>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/homefleet/shipsj.html |title=Norwegian Homefleet \u2013 WW II, Ships starting with J |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=9 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Hokuan I-Go||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The salvage vessel was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Strait of Malacca]] by {{HMS|Taurus|P399|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|ST|Kainan Maru No. 15||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[tugboat|tug]] was torpedoed and sunk in the Strait of Malacca by {{HMS|Taurus|P399|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese transport|Koryu Maru||2}} \