boat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1756.html |title=Solvoll |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=17 April 2012}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==14 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=14 April 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|B\u00e4renfels|1921|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The cargo ship struck [[naval mine|mines]] and sank in the [[Norwegian Sea]] off [[Bergen]], Norway.<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=5605537|shipname=Barenfels |accessdate=19 July 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Baroda||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[File:Bombay-Docks-aftermath3.png|thumb|One of the ships damaged in the Bombay Explosion]][[Bombay Explosion (1944)|Bombay Explosion]]: The [[cargo liner]] was lost as a result of the explosion of ''Fort Stikine'' ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}) at [[Bombay]], [[British Raj|India]].<ref name=\"Ships lost in the Bombay explosion\">{{cite web |url=http://merchantships.tripod.com/fortcreviershipslost.html |title=Ships lost in the Bombay explosion |publisher=tripod |accessdate=14 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMHS|Chantilly|63|6}}\n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Bombay Explosion (1944)|Bombay Explosion]]: The [[hospital ship]] was severely damaged by the explosion of ''Fort Stikine'' ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}) at [[Bombay]], [[British Raj|India]]. She was subsequently repaired and returned to service.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMIS|El Hind}} \n|flag={{navy|British India}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Bombay Explosion (1944)|Bombay Explosion]]: The [[Landing ship infantry|landing ship infantry (large)]] was burned out as a result of the explosion of ''Fort Stikine'' ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}) at [[Bombay]], [[British India|India]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/13447.html |title=Landing Ship Infantry HMIS El Hind |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=14 April 2013}}</ref>\n}