erenceB\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/russia/ru_cf_ya5.htm |title=Ya-5 class motor mortar boats, USSR |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=29 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet mortar motor boat|Ya-27||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=The ''Ya-5''-class mortar motor boat was lost on this date.<ref name=\"ReferenceB\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==19 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=19 April 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Embla||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Sweden}}\n|desc=[[File:Red Cross.png|40px]][[International Committee of the Red Cross|Red Cross]]: [[World War II]]: The Red Cross-marked cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] off [[S\u00e8te]], [[H\u00e9rault]], France by [[Bristol Beaufighter]] aircraft of [[Royal Air Force]]. All 21 crew survived the attack.<ref name=seekrieg194404/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://octopus-plongee.asso.fr/index.php/nos-sites-de-plongee/68-lembla-dit-le-suedois |title=Embla |publisher=octopus-plongee.asso.fr |accessdate=19 April 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 622||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The Type C2 ''[[Marinef\u00e4hrprahm]]'' was sunk by Allied fighter-bombers off [[Piombino]], Italy.<ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.historisches-marinearchiv.de/projekte/landungsfahrzeuge/marinefaehrprahm/ausgabe.php?where_value=787 |title=F 622 |publisher=www.historisches-marinearchiv.de |accessdate=19 April 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 4760||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The [[F-lighter|MZ-A landing craft]] was sunk by Allied fighter-bombers off [[Piombino]], Italy. One crew was killed.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_mz.htm |title=MZ type small landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hi