r|cargo ship|2}} was torpedoed and damaged in [[Milne Bay]], [[New Guinea]], by Japanese aircraft. She consequently became a [[hulk (ship)|storage hulk]].\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Genbu Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: Convoy OKI-509: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] ({{coord|27|16|N|128|21|E}}) by the [[submarine]] {{USS|Halibut|SS-232|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}). Two troops and a crewman were killed.<ref name=Halibut/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese minelayer|Kamome||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: Convoy OKI-509: The {{sclass-|Tsubame|minelayer}} was torpedoed and sunk in the Pacific Ocean ({{coord|27|03|N|128|06|E}}) by the [[submarine]] {{USS|Halibut|SS-232|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=Halibut/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|M 3668||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[minesweeper]], a  KFK-class [[naval drifter]], struck a mine and sank in the [[North Sea]] off [[Ostend]], [[West Flanders]], [[Belgium]].<ref name=seekrieg194404/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet motor torpedo boat|TK-332||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The G-5-class [[motor torpedo boat]] was shelled and sunk by German and Romanian surface ships in the [[black sea]].<ref name=\"G-5 class motor torpedo boat, USSR\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/russia/ru_cf_g5.htm |title=G-5 class motor torpedo boat, USSR |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=27 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Soviet Naval Losses Black Sea\">{{cite web |url=http://www.soviet-empire.com/ussr/viewtopic.php?f=149&t=53917&sid=0225559cd69b51f93f8b0cfbfab11342 |title=Soviet Naval Losses (Black Sea)|publisher=Sovietempire.com |accessdate=3 April 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-803||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type IX submarine|Type IXC/40]] [